</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D318 height=3D193
src=3D"GameConcepts_CombatInvasion_files/image002.png" align=3Dright hspace=
=3D12
v:shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_14"><![endif]><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>In=
vading
an enemy colony involves landing ground troops from your ships. Once landed
your troops then battle it out with any defending troops of the other empir=
e.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Note that you can dis=
play a
detailed animated view of ground battles by opening the Ground Report scree=
n.
To open this screen first select the colony in the Selection Panel, then cl=
ick
the Troops area in the Selection Panel.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h3><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Initiating an invasion<o:p></o:p></spa=
n></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>To initiate an invasi=
on of an
enemy colony, select one of your troop-carrying ships, or even an entire fl=
eet.
Then right-click on an enemy colony to attack it. Any ships carrying troops
will attempt to deploy them in an invasion.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>To land your invasion=
 troops
requires your ships to get close to the colony. You have two options in this
case:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpFirst style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l=
0 level1 lfo2'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol;mso-no-proof:yes'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Attempt an
immediate invasion without regard to any enemy defences at the colony (i.e.
enemy military ships, space ports, etc). <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoListParagraphCxSpLast style=3D'text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0=
 level1 lfo2'><![if !supportLists]><span
style=3D'font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fa=
mily:
Symbol;mso-no-proof:yes'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span
style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=
&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>First clear=
 any
enemy defences and then land your troops unopposed. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Both of these strateg=
ies have
advantages and disadvantages.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h3><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Immediate Invasion<o:p></o:p></span></=
h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_15" o:=
spid=3D"_x0000_s1026"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-left:89.7pt;margin-=
top:0;
 width:140.9pt;height:130.05pt;z-index:251658240;visibility:visible;
 mso-wrap-style:square;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent:0;
 mso-wrap-distance-left:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right=
:9pt;
 mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;mso-position-horizontal:right;
 mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;mso-position-vertical:absolute;
 mso-position-vertical-relative:text;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent=
:0;
 mso-width-relative:page;mso-height-relative:page'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"GameConcepts_CombatInvasion_files/image003.png" o:titl=
e=3D""/>
 <w:wrap type=3D"square"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D188 height=3D173
src=3D"GameConcepts_CombatInvasion_files/image004.png" align=3Dright hspace=
=3D12
v:shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_15"><![endif]><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Im=
mediate
invasion may mean a quick win for your invading troops, ending ground comba=
t.
In the event of your forces winning the ground battle and taking the colony,
any enemy bases at the colony immediately become yours also. This only leav=
es
enemy ships for your attacking forces to destroy or chase away.<o:p></o:p><=
/span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>However immediate inv=
asion
carries a high risk that your invading ships will be destroyed before they =
can
get close enough to deploy their troops. In this case both the ships and the
troops they contain are lost. This possibility is especially high when the
colony is defended by a space port.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h3><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Clearing Enemy Defences First<o:p></o:=
p></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Clearing enemy defenc=
es prior
to invasion minimizes the risk to your invading troops, but requires greater
exposure of your military ships as they bombard any defending space ports a=
nd
battle enemy ships.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Large defensive bases=
 such as
space ports should always be attacked in force &#8211; usually by an entire
fleet. Anything less will doom your assault to failure, as the heavily defe=
nded
and armed base picks off your inadequate forces</span></p>

</div>

